# Drop your operator-invoked scripts here.
#
# This folder is bind-mounted to /opt/airflow/scripts inside the
# airflow-webserver and airflow-scheduler containers. A BashOperator
# can invoke files placed here, for example:
#
#   BashOperator(
#       task_id="transform",
#       bash_command="python /opt/airflow/scripts/transform.py {{ ds }}",
#   )
#
# Files appear inside the containers immediately on save (no rebuild).
#
# DAG definition files (.py with `with DAG(...):` blocks) belong in
# ../dags/, not here. The Airflow scheduler scans dags/ every ~30 s
# looking for DAG objects to register; scripts in this folder are
# only read at task run time when an operator references them by path.
